00:20:06,638 --> 00:20:11,591
But the bottom down there got long, and I braided the end.

176
00:20:11,885 --> 00:20:14,490
This is done well.

177
00:20:14,490 --> 00:20:15,851
And the bottom here?

178
00:20:17,977 --> 00:20:20,497
This is made very well.

179
00:20:21,036 --> 00:20:27,830
Please hold it, connecting the bottom parts, showing the bottom.

180
00:20:37,545 --> 00:20:40,683
They would also weave grass to make fish carrying bags.

181
00:20:40,683 --> 00:20:45,725
When they didn’t have paper boxes, they always made bags for fish.

182
00:20:46,182 --> 00:20:48,975
And the dry fish they made would be good.

183
00:20:49,390 --> 00:20:52,740
They would weave grass with this close pattern.

184
00:20:54,196 --> 00:20:56,706
They called those kuusqulluut.

185
00:20:57,665 --> 00:21:05,710
Their openings would be woven, the grass would be woven to make ropes.

186
00:21:05,803 --> 00:21:09,071
Would the aged herring be in them as well?

187
00:21:09,210 --> 00:21:15,180
We didn’t have aged herring. I’m from [the] tundra.

188
00:21:16,780 --> 00:21:22,580
And caches, every family would have a cache.

189
00:21:24,024 --> 00:21:27,598
Fish cache, and it would have wooden posts.

190
00:21:27,890 --> 00:21:31,211
